-- Spanish Stocks Advance, Led by Ferrovial, ACS, Sniace; Abertis Declines
-- Alexis Xydias
-- 2010-07-23T09:26:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/spanish-stocks-advance-led-by-ferrovial-acs-sniace-abertis-declines.html

          
          
             Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  rose 14.7, or
0.1 percent, to 10,317.6 as of 11:24 a.m. in Madrid. The  Madrid
Stock Exchange General Index  gained 0.1 percent to 1,066.66.  
 The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market today.  
      Abertis Infraestructuras SA  (ABE SM) fell 3 percent to
13.46 euros. La Caixa, the owner of Abertis shareholder Criteria
CaixaCorp SA, is considering dropping plans to carry out a
buyout of Abertis with CVC Capital Partners Ltd. and  Actividades
de Construccion y Servicios SA  (ACS SM), El Confidencial said.
ACS rose 0.3 percent to 32.67 euros.  
      Ferrovial SA  (FER SM) rose 2.4 percent to 6.65 euros. The
builder and airport operator was added to Credit Suisse Group
AG’s “European Focus List” of favorite stocks in the region.  
 Sniace SA  (SNC SM) jumped 5.4 percent to 1.19 euros. The
paper company reported first-half profit of 2.23 million euros
($2.9 million) compared with a 1.97 million-euro loss a year
ago.  
